      • withKeysDomain

        public ByteHashConfig withKeysDomain(byte minPossibleKey,
                            byte maxPossibleKey)
        Returns byte hash config with the specified keys domain.

        This is a performance hint, hash containers could, but aren't required to throw IllegalArgumentException on putting key out of the specified domain.

        Example: 

         // only positive keys
 conf = conf.withKeysDomain(1, Byte.MAX_VALUE);
        Returns:
        byte hash config with the specified keys domain
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if minPossibleKey is greater than maxPossibleKey

      • withKeysDomainComplement

        public ByteHashConfig withKeysDomainComplement(byte minImpossibleKey,
                                      byte maxImpossibleKey)
        Returns byte hash config with the specified keys domain complement.

        Example: 

         // any keys except 0

        Returns:
